recipeIngredient: 250g leftover roast chicken, roughly diced, skin and bones removed
2 medium carrots, peeled and small diced

recipeInstructions.text: Put the oil in a pan, gently saut√© the garlic, onion, potato and carrot till softened and slightly caramelised, Stir through Spinach and cook a further 2 mins or so until u can break it apart in the pan. Preheat oven to 160C fan forced or 170C normal.
In a large bowl, throw in the eggs, seasoning, chicken, and the cooked vegetables
Stir through the basil, the parmesan and brie, till all combined.
Pour into a greased spring form pan and place it in preheated oven till golden and set, approximately 30 minutes.
